rComments: Great Prof... IF you ask questions he will answer. If you need help he will always help you... Always willing to give a hand to you... Man You can tell he tries to make you become a good student. Just ask him and he will find time for you.. Dont be afraid to go up to him and ask after the lecture is over. He will make things clear for you.
Giving easy tests to make up for poor teaching and inability to understand peoples questions does not make for a decent professor.

This guy taught his lectures at 8pm on friday. He worded the question of the midterm differently, so many people failed, even though the question was simple. Final exam was a gift. He photocopies the textbook and reads it. I stopped attending his class. He offered to help me on the weekend, so he does care about students. Boring, avoid.

His slides are just photocopies from the textbook.  His actual lecture isn't bad, he just takes forever to cover anything, and gives you stupid busy work to do during the DGDs.  We're three weeks in and we've done absolutely nothing.  It's too bad, the textbook is really interesting.
